entries.femaleVariant: Christine Markov?
You Christine Markov? We have some questions.
You badges?
Who're we talkin' to?
So, who're we supposed to talk to?
Cyberpsycho's boss, you said?
We mighta guessed as much.
Might've expected as much.
OK, Red Queen's Race now.
I'll talk to my CI about your club – Red Queen's Race.

entries.femaleVariant: Your friend'll be out after the election.
Gentlemen, please.
Fuck off, scopshitters.

Right. You did lose your only associate who could string two sentences together. Too bad he also liked diddling little kids.
<kiroshi l="jpn" o="今回は見逃してやるよ、ウォード。だが、次はないからな" t="We'll let it go this time, Ward. But this time's the last time." b="" a=""/>
Fuck off, kitty claws.
Goddammit, V. Told you I'd handle it.
Got a problem with everyone, or just Tygers?
Ugh... Gotta report this.
Good thing nobody got killed.
Little less paperwork.
First, I gotta clean up the mess you made.
Gonna ride with me?
Meet you there.
Sure, coming with you.
Meet you there.
Sure, coming with you.
How about we change tacks this time? Ask questions first, then level threats?
A good ninety percent of any detective's job is talking.
Christine Markov, forty-two. File has her as Horváth's sole employer.
But you know that already. Must say, you're kinda a natural.
Sole contact, too, actually.
NCPD. This is Detective Ward.
Yep.
Nope.
We're here about Péter Horváth.
No, not cops. Just lookin' for some intel.
Lookin' for data on Péter Horváth.
Yeah, he did. Then he stopped workin', started makin' fuckin' speeches all the time.
Everyone's always lookin' for somethin'. Least I know where I stand with the cops.
Other people? Open your mouth one day, corpo muscle or gangoons show up on your doorstep the next…
Péter Horváth. Worked for you, right?
Worked here, apparently.
Whaddaya want?
Péter Horváth – know he worked here.
Speeches? What'd he say?
He make good scratch here?
Erratic behavior – when'd it start?
These speeches – what'd he have to say?
entries.maleVariant: These, uh, speeches – what'd he have to say?

entries.femaleVariant: Horváth make good scratch here? Coulda bought this whole market with the chrome he was packin'.
When'd the weird behavior actually start?
"Rhyne – corps got him by the balls and cock, but he still managed to fuck me." His motto.
Why'd he have it in for the mayor?
Hah, lookin' for reason in that whackjob? Prolly thought Rhyne was talkin' to him through the TV, promisin' all sorts of shit, then ceasin' to give a fuck.
Look, I told you what I think. In Horváth's world, everybody was out to get him. Lucius Rhyne was out to fuck him, then get him.
Look, when you're talkin' about Péter, "weird" doesn't mean what it means for everybody else. Horváth never was completely normal.
But the post-jail Horváth versus the pre-jail Horváth? Gonks both, but completely different gonks.
Ah-haha! Oh yeah, made scads on scads here, ahaha. Motherfuckin' millionaire, like we all are.
So where'd he get the eddies? Know anything?
Look, if I knew, I wouldn't be here sellin' scop to tower trash. I'd get myself an AV, fly my fuckin' slim ass outta here.
Péter showed up one day with all that. Extra worked up too. Whacked enough that I asked him where he got it. He said somebody'd finally seen what he was worth.
Then he launched right into one of his tirades.
"Somebody'd finally seen what he was worth." Horváth had sponsors.
So Horváth had a personal beef with Rhyne.
Didn't learn a lot.
Don't think we learned much of anything new.
Might seem like we didn't get a lot out of that.
But sometimes intel makes sense once you got some context.
Say, for instance, somebody says they got a headache.
Minor detail, means nothing, right? Usually, sure.
But then the guy waltzes straight into oncoming traffic. The neighbor remembers someone had worked on the air conditioner in the guy's unit, guy whose head always hurt.
Accident? Coincidence? Or maybe air-dispersed poison. A deliberate hit.
You actually caught a case like that?
No. Made it up. Still proves my point.

Gentlemen, gentlemen. Chill, please.

entries.femaleVariant: Heh. Jump, clown! Jump!
Step aside, Lugg. Your boyfriend got sent up for years. Doubt you want the same.
Arrest was for show. They'll let 'im out soon.
Walkin' the streets with you – downright unsafe. Got a beef with all gangs or just the Tygers?
I'm a cop. Whaddaya think?
We'll meet there.
Assuming you're still on board.
You kiddin'?
Meet you there.
Sure, I'll ride with you.
Fine by me.
Who're we talkin' to this time?
Other ten percent – what's it made of?
And the other ten percent? What's it consist of?
Writing reports.
You know Christine Markov?
Christine Markov?
Christine Markov – know her? Has a stall here.
You Christine Markov?
Christine Markov. Where'll I find her?
I don't know her. You buying somethin'? If not, get out.
You Christine Markov?
Me? No. She's over there. Stall with the tech.
Thanks.
Know which one. Let's go.
No idea who we're looking for. Gonna have to ask around.
Had to be some other connection between them.
Had no other connection, those two? Think hard.
So as Horváth saw it, who else had it in for him?
Horváth single anyone else out, who had it in for him?
Easy money – that's what Horváth was after. Didn't do time for nothin'.
Worked for normals, not so normals. Gah, maybe he and Rhyne had some mutual friends?
Will that be all, detectives? You're spookin' my clientele.
'Sides Rhyne? Uh, Madame President, mostly.
Then Arasaka, the geezer, and when he died it was his son's turn.
I'll start from the left, you take the right.
No. But I know who she is. Stand with the tech, over on the other side.
Don't know any Christine. This isn't BD Heads Anonymous.
[Get out]
[Sit and wait]
